The Museum of Contemporary Art (MoCA) in New York has released the list of fifty artists who will participate in the third edition of the museum’s “Artist’s Town,” which will take place at Pacific Palisades Park from September 17 to October 3, 2020. The nearly three hundred invited artists were selected from a pool of fifteen artists who exhibited at the museum last year. The artists chosen for the event are as follows:● Alighiero Bagnoni, Los Angeles;

● Katherine Graham, New York;

● Fred Melby, New York;

● Pierre Huyghe, New York;

● Rene Magritte, New York;

● Thomas Peterson, New York;

● George Barlow, New York;

● Paul Gauguin, New York;

● A.A. Milne, New York;

● David Silverman, New York;

● Willem de Kooning, New York;
